# Spec-Kit SDD Workflow

Use Spec-Driven Development for new work in this repository.

## Primary Workflow
- Quick path: `/brief [task-id] [description]`
- Full path: `/research` -> `/specify` -> `/plan` -> `/tasks` -> `/implement`
- Save new planning artifacts in `specs/active/[task-id]/`
- Use `.sdd/templates/` for concise outputs

## Historical Context
- Project history migrated from the legacy workflow now lives in `specs/00-overview.md` and `specs/completed/`.
- Prefer `specs/completed/hydration-phase1/`, `specs/completed/v1-0-0-release/`, and `specs/completed/legacy-memory-bank/` when older context is needed.

## Working Rules
- Keep this always-applied rule thin. Load details from `.cursor/commands/`, `.cursor/agents/`, `.cursor/skills/`, and `.sdd/` on demand.
- For non-trivial work, plan before editing.
- Use subagents when they reduce main-context bloat.
- Validate implementation with readback, lints, tests, or review steps as appropriate.

## Key References
- Commands: `.cursor/commands/`
- Agents: `.cursor/agents/`
- Skills: `.cursor/skills/`
- Config and templates: `.sdd/`
- Specs index: `specs/index.md`
- Migration notes: `.sdd/MIGRATION.md`
